cs.MA, cs.RO, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.DC 

This paper proposes a framework for robotic multiagent systems that involves both mobility and communication, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. However, the focus on multiagent systems and the use of artificial potentials for motion planning suggest that cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) is the most likely sub-category. The use of fast multipole networks for communication and their efficiency in a distributed setting suggest that cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) are also likely sub-categories. The fact that the paper deals with a unified framework for both mobility and communication suggests that cs.SY (Systems and Control) could also be a relevant sub-category. Finally, the use of fast multipole networks for communication could also suggest cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) as a possible sub-category.
